org.cloudgraph.mapreduce

Class GraphXmlMapper<KEYOUT,VALUEOUT>

  • java.lang.Object
      • org.cloudgraph.mapreduce.GraphXmlMapper<KEYOUT,VALUEOUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    KEYOUT - the output key type
    VALUEOUT - the output value type

    public class GraphXmlMapper<KEYOUT,VALUEOUT>
extends
    Supplies fully realized data graphs as the input value to MapReduce Mapper client subclasses, the input key being an offset into the processed file and the value being a GraphWritable assembled from a single SDO graph XML line read from the file. Supports detection of changes to the input data graph, and propagation of mutations to the underlying data store. The data graphs supplied to the code>Mapper are ready to further modify or simply commit as is, for Mapper clients wishing to modify input graphs and commit changes within the map phase. See the below code sample based on the Wikipedia domain model which adds a page link to each input graph. 

    public class PageGraphImporter extends GraphXmlMapper {
